race.comment: MAISON LOUIS (2) talented gelding who drifted further back than expected and never comfortable in the soft (7) going when a disappointing twelfth over 2000m in the G3 Rosehill Gold Cup at Randwick. Pulled up with a cough on that occasion and can redeem himself out to the 2300m. GRAND PIERRO (6) brings the right form from Victoria after finishing a respectable fifth in the G2 Moonee Valley Cup. Drops in weight and gets every chance. FUTURE HISTORY (3) fifth-up here and looking for this trip now. Strong through the line when fourth in the G3 JRA Cup at Moonee Valley. Will roll forward and give plenty of cheek. WYCLIF (8) back in grade and doesn't have to improve much to take a hand in the finish. Finished an unlucky fourth over this track and trip in the Newcastle Cup three-back. Respect. AGE OF SAIL (9) trained locally and happy to pen last start, when everything went wrong from the draw in the G3 Bendigo Cup. Can sit off them and surge late at the good odds.
